('dgms-legis-2017-mines-rules-1955-amendment-ease-of-compliance-for-registers','DGMS Legislative Circular 2017 — Mines Rules 1955 Amendment for Ease of Compliance in Maintaining Registers','dgms_circular','Communicates the amendment to the Mines Rules, 1955 giving effect to the "Ease of Compliance to Maintain Registers under Various Labour Laws Rules, 2017", which replaces 56 overlapping registers and forms across nine central Acts with just 5 common registers/forms.',null,'DGMS','2017','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Ease_of_compliance_to_maintain_registers_under_Labour_Laws_Rules_2017.pdf','Ease_of_compliance_to_maintain_registers_under_Labour_Laws_Rules_2017.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('dgms-legis-2019-equal-employment-opportunity-for-women-in-mines','DGMS Legislative Circular 2019 — Equal Employment Opportunity for Women in Mines','dgms_circular','Notifies the Central Government''s exemption of women employed above and below ground in mines from Section 46 of the Mines Act, 1952, and requires mine owners to frame and implement a standard operating procedure (per the annexed guidelines) for employing women underground and during night hours in opencast/aboveground mines.',null,'DGMS','2019','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMSLegiCircula_2019.pdf','DGMSLegiCircula_2019.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('dgms-tech-04-2020-inflammable-gas-hazard-prevention-in-coal-mines','DGMS Technical Circular 04/2020 — Prevention of Inflammable Gas Hazards in Belowground Coal Mines','dgms_circular','Reviews the adequacy of the Coal Mines Regulations, 2017 and prescribes measures to safeguard mineworkers against methane ignition and explosion hazards in belowground coal mines, with particular reference to the highly gassy Jharia and Raniganj seams.',null,'DGMS','2020-02-27','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMS_04637184121810426988.pdf','DGMS_04637184121810426988.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('dgms-tech-08-2020-12th-national-conference-on-safety-in-mines-recommendations','DGMS Technical Circular 08/2020 — Recommendations of the 12th National Conference on Safety in Mines','dgms_circular','Circulates the recommendations of the 12th National Conference on Safety in Mines (New Delhi, 28-29 January 2020) covering electrical safety, information technology in mining, pneumoconiosis/silicosis and dust control, disaster prevention in coal mines, and safety and health of contractual workers.',null,'DGMS','2020-04-29','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/llssa.pdf','llssa.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('dgms-tech-2017-dust-suppression-device-approval-for-coal-mines','DGMS Technical Circular 2017 — Dust Suppression Device Approval for Coal Mines','dgms_circular','Brings the approval of dust suppression/prevention devices fitted in drilling and boring equipment used in coal mines under Regulation 123(6)(b)(ii) of the Coal Mines Regulations, 1957 into a general approval scheme with finalized standards for their manufacture, testing and use.',null,'DGMS','2017','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Dus_tsuppresson.pdf','Dus_tsuppresson.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('delegation-of-power-of-central-government-to-rlcs-under-section-59-1-for-issue-of-recovery','Delegation of Recovery-Certificate Power to Regional Labour Commissioners under Section 59(1) of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2320(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 100 of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020 delegating to Regional Labour Commissioners (Central), within their jurisdiction, the power under Section 59(1) to issue recovery certificates.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Delegation of power of Central Government to RLCs under section 59(1) for issue of Recovery Certificate under the Industrial Relations Code 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('delegation-of-power-of-central-government-under-section-87-1-under-chapter-xiii-for-filing','Delegation of Power to File Court Complaints under Section 87(1) of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2319(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 100 of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020 directing that the Section 87(1) power to file complaints in courts for certain Chapter XIII offences (under sub-sections (4), (6) and (12) to (19) of Section 86) may also be exercised by specified Central Labour Commissioners within their jurisdictions.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Delegation of power of Central Government under section 87(1) under Chapter XIII for filing complaints in the Courts for certain offences under the Industrial Relations Code 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('draft-code-on-wages-central-rules-2025','Draft Code on Wages (Central) Rules, 2025','labour_code','Draft rules notified as G.S.R. 936(E) on 30 December 2025 under Section 67 of the Code on Wages, 2019, inviting objections and suggestions, and proposed to replace earlier payment-of-wages, minimum-wages and related central rules following commencement of all provisions of the Code.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2025','superseded','Draft superseded by the final Code on Wages (Central) Rules, 2026 (published 8 May 2026).','https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Draft Code on Wages (Central) Rules, 2025.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('draft-industrial-relations-code-central-rules-2025','Draft Industrial Relations Code (Central) Rules, 2025','labour_code','Draft rules notified as G.S.R. 930(E) on 30 December 2025 under Section 99 of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020, inviting objections and suggestions, and proposed to replace the Industrial Disputes (Central) Rules, 1957 and the Industrial Employment (Standing Orders) Central Rules, 1946 following commencement of all provisions of the Code.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2025','superseded','Draft superseded by the final IR Code (Central) Rules, 2026 (published 8 May 2026).','https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Draft Industrial Relations Code (Central) Rules, 2025.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('draft-occupational-safety-health-and-working-conditions-code-central-rules-2025','Draft Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions Code (Central) Rules, 2025','labour_code','Draft rules notified as G.S.R. 934(E) on 30 December 2025 under Sections 133 and 134 of the Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions Code, 2020, inviting objections and suggestions, and proposed to supersede several existing safety and welfare rules including the Mines Rules, 1955, Mines Rescue Rules, 1985 and Mines Vocational Training Rules.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2025','superseded','Draft superseded by the final OSH&WC Code (Central) Rules, 2026 (published 8 May 2026).','https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Draft Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions Code (Central) Rules, 2025.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('draft-social-security-code-central-rules-2025','Draft Code on Social Security (Central) Rules, 2025','labour_code','Draft rules notified as G.S.R. 935(E) on 30 December 2025 under Sections 154, 155, 158 and 159 of the Code on Social Security, 2020, inviting objections and suggestions, following commencement of all provisions of the Code.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2025','superseded','Draft superseded by the final Social Security Code (Central) Rules, 2026 (published 8 May 2026).','https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Draft Social Security Code (Central) Rules, 2025.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('industrial-relations-code-jharkhand-notification','Industrial Relations Code, 2020 - Jharkhand Transfer of Pending Cases Notification','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 5683(E), dated 8 December 2025) issued in connection with Sections 51 and 104 of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020, providing for the transfer of cases pending before labour courts and tribunals under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 to the corresponding tribunals under the new Code upon its commencement on 21 November 2025.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2021','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','IR_Code_Jharkhand_Notification.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('notification-of-the-code-on-social-security-2020-in-the-gazette-of-india-part-ii-section-3','Exemption of Low-Wage Vacancies from Section 139 Reporting under the Code on Social Security, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2343(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 140(2)(b) of the Code on Social Security, 2020 providing that the vacancy-reporting requirement of Section 139 shall not apply to vacancies carrying total remuneration of less than eleven thousand rupees per month.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification of the Code on Social Security 2020 in the Gazette of India Part II Section 3 Sub Section (ii) regarding.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('notification-regarding-executive-officer-for-the-purposes-of-chapter-xiii','Executive Officer for Chapter XIII of the Code on Social Security, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2344(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 2(30) of the Code on Social Security, 2020 designating the Joint Director or Director (Employment) overseeing the Career Centre (Central) in the Directorate General of Employment as the executive officer to discharge duties under Chapter XIII of the Code.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment',null,'in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification regarding executive officer for the purposes of Chapter XIII.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('notification-under-section-122-of-coss-2020','Appointment of Inspectors-cum-Facilitators under Section 122 of the Code on Social Security, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2356(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 122(1) of the Code on Social Security, 2020 appointing Social Security Officers, Assistant Directors, Deputy Directors, Regional Directors, Additional Commissioners and Insurance Commissioners as Inspectors-cum-Facilitators for Chapter IV and related provisions of the Code.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification under Section 122 of CoSS, 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('notification-under-section-127-of-coss-2020','Interest on Delayed Contributions under Section 127 of the Code on Social Security, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2357(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 127 of the Code on Social Security, 2020 specifying that employers shall pay simple interest at twelve percent per annum on any contribution or amount due from the date it becomes payable until the date of actual payment.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification under Section 127 of CoSS, 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('notification-under-section-128-of-coss-2020','Authorisation of Officers to Recover Damages under Section 128 of the Code on Social Security, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2358(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 128 of the Code on Social Security, 2020 authorising Insurance Commissioners, Additional Commissioners, Regional Directors and Deputy Directors to exercise powers and functions relating to recovery of damages under Chapter IV within their assigned jurisdictions.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification under Section 128 of CoSS, 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('notification-under-section-136-1-of-coss-2020','Authorisation to Institute and Defend Legal Proceedings under Section 136(1) of the Code on Social Security, 2020','labour_code','Central Government notification (S.O. 2359(E), dated 8 May 2026) issued under Section 136(1) of the Code on Social Security, 2020 authorising the ESIC Director General and a range of specified officers to institute suits and other legal proceedings on behalf of the Corporation and to defend proceedings against it before courts and tribunals.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification under Section 136(1) of CoSS, 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
