('notification-under-section-44-of-coss-2020','Notification under Section 44 of the Code on Social Security, 2020 (Medical Facility Scheme for Other Beneficiaries, 2026)','labour_code','This notification (S.O. 2355(E), 8 May 2026) frames the Medical Facility Scheme, 2026, extending ESI-style medical treatment and care to other beneficiaries and their family members registered under schemes other than the Employees'' State Insurance Scheme.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification under Section 44 of CoSS, 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('notification-under-section-9-2-of-coss-2020','Notification under Section 9(2) of the Code on Social Security, 2020 (Authentication of ESIC Orders and Decisions)','labour_code','This notification (S.O. 2354(E), 8 May 2026) specifies that all orders and decisions of the Employees'' State Insurance Corporation shall be authenticated by the Director General or other authorised officers such as the Insurance Commissioner, Additional Commissioner, Regional Directors, Joint Directors and Deputy Directors.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Notification under Section 9 (2) of CoSS, 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('osh-wc-central-rules-2026-dgms-copy-12-05-2026','Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions (Central) Rules, 2026 (DGMS Copy, 12 May 2026)','labour_code','This notification (G.S.R. 345(E), 8 May 2026) brings into force the OSH&WC (Central) Rules, 2026 under Sections 133 and 134 of the OSH&WC Code, 2020, superseding numerous earlier rules including the Mines Rules 1955, Mines Rescue Rules 1985, Mines Vocational Training Rules 1966 and Contract Labour Central Rules 1971.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2026','in_force','Final central rules published 8 May 2026 (DGMS copy).','https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/CentralRule_12052026.pdf','CentralRule_12052026.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('occupational-safety-health-wc-jharkhand-rules-2021-state-rule-mine-relevant','Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions (Jharkhand) Rules, 2021 [State rule; mine-relevant]','labour_code','This Jharkhand Gazette notification (S.O. 05, 27 August 2021) publishes draft state OSH&WC Rules under Sections 134 and 135 of the OSH&WC Code, 2020, superseding earlier Jharkhand rules on factories, building and construction workers, contract labour, inter-state migrant workers and motor transport workers, and invites objections within 45 days.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2021','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','OSH_Jharkhand_Rules_2021.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('publication-of-notification-of-the-code-on-social-security-2020-in-the-gazette-of-india-pa','Notification under Sections 136(2) and 138(1) of the Code on Social Security, 2020 (Authorised Officers for Prosecution and Compounding of Career Centre Offences)','labour_code','This notification (S.O. 2342(E), 8 May 2026) authorises specified officers of the Career Centres — the Director (Employment) and Joint Director (Employment) — to sanction prosecution and compound offences under Chapter XIII of the Code on Social Security, 2020 across all of India.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Publication of Notification of the Code on Social Security 2020 in the Gazette of India Part II Section 3 Sub Section (ii) regarding.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('publication-of-notification-of-the-code-on-social-security-2020-regarding-career-centre','Notification under Section 139(1) of the Code on Social Security, 2020 (Employer Reporting of Vacancies to Career Centres)','labour_code','This notification (S.O. 2341(E), 8 May 2026) fixes the date, ninety days after notification of the Social Security (Central) Rules, 2026, from which every public- and private-sector establishment must report its vacancies to the concerned Career Centre.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Publication of Notification of the Code on Social Security 2020 regarding Career Centre.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('setting-up-of-reskilling-fund-under-section-83-1-of-ir-code-2020','Notification under Section 83(1) of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020 (Setting up of the Worker Re-skilling Fund)','labour_code','This notification (S.O. 2316(E), 8 May 2026) establishes the Worker Re-skilling Fund for the purposes of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020, which finances retraining of retrenched workers.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Setting up of Reskilling Fund under section 83 (1) of IR Code 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('specifying-gazetted-officers-for-compounding-of-offences-under-section-89-1-of-the-industr','Notification under Section 89(1) of the Industrial Relations Code, 2020 (Officers Empowered to Compound Offences)','labour_code','This notification (S.O. 2317(E), 8 May 2026) designates the Chief Labour Commissioner (Central), Additional and Deputy Chief Labour Commissioners across specified regional jurisdictions as the gazetted officers empowered to compound offences under the Industrial Relations Code, 2020 for establishments where the Central Government is the appropriate government.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Specifying Gazetted Officers for Compounding of Offences under section 89(1) of the Industrial Relations Code 2020.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('withdrawal-of-cmr-2017-competency-bye-laws-23-03-2026','Withdrawal of Board of Mining Examinations Bye-laws on Gas Testing Certificates under the Coal Mines Regulations, 2017 (16 March 2026)','cmr_2017','This DGMS notification (G.S.R. 187(E), 16 March 2026) rescinds, with immediate effect, the Board of Mining Examinations bye-laws (G.S.R. 491(E) dated 22 July 2025) governing the grant of Gas Testing Certificates of Competency under Regulations 12(1) and 12(4) of the Coal Mines Regulations, 2017.',null,'DGMS','2026','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/WithdrawaCMR_2017_GN_23032026.pdf','WithdrawaCMR_2017_GN_23032026.pdf',2,220,true,false),
('additional-faqs-on-labour-codes','Additional FAQs on the Labour Codes (as on 16 March 2026)','labour_code','This Ministry of Labour and Employment FAQ clarifies interpretive questions on the four Labour Codes, including how overtime, gratuity, PF contributions and statutory bonus are treated in computing the 50 percent wage floor under the Code on Wages, 2019, and wage-protection provisions for white-collar employees.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment',null,'in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Additional FAQs on Labour Codes.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('booklet-new-labour-code-for-new-india','Booklet: New Labour Code for New India','labour_code','This government booklet presents the four Labour Codes as the biggest labour reforms since independence, explaining how they universalise minimum wages, ensure timely payment of wages, prioritise occupational safety, and extend social security while reducing compliance burden.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment',null,'in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Booklet- New Labour Code for New India.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('compliance-handbook-for-employers','Compliance Handbook for Employers under the Four Labour Codes (Central Government Sphere)','labour_code','This handbook guides employers through their obligations under the Code on Wages 2019, the Industrial Relations Code 2020, the OSH&WC Code 2020 and the Code on Social Security 2020, with chapter-wise action points, key definitions and relevant schedules.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment',null,'in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Compliance Handbook for Employers.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-03-2017-accident-occurrence-alert-procedures','DGMS 03/2017 — Alert on Occurrence of Accidents','dgms_circular','Advises owners, agents and managers of coal mines to regularly monitor the "Alert/Hazard" menu on the DGMS website, where accident and incident alerts are uploaded, so remedial measures can be taken to prevent recurrence of similar accidents.',null,'DGMS','2017','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/CIR_03_Tech_MAMID.pdf','CIR_03_Tech_MAMID.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-1-2023-jurisdiction-of-zones-and-regions-of-dgms-after-reorganisation','DGMS General Circular 01/2023 — Jurisdiction of Zones and Regions of DGMS after Reorganisation','dgms_circular','Sets out the revised jurisdiction of the zones and regional offices of DGMS following reorganisation notified vide G.S.R. 300(E) dated 17 April 2023, detailing the constitution of the Central Zone and its Dhanbad and Koderma regions across Bihar and Jharkhand.',null,'DGMS','2023-05-18','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMScircular1_2023.pdf','DGMScircular1_2023.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-1-2024-examination-related-circular','DGMS (Legis.)(Exam) Circular 01/2024 — Issue of Statutory Certificates in Online/Digital Mode','dgms_circular','Informs stakeholders that the Board of Mining Examinations is issuing statutory certificates under the Coal Mines Regulations 2017, Metalliferous Mines Regulations 1961 and Mines Act 1952 on both examination and exemption basis in online/digital mode, and provides links to verify such certificates online.',null,'DGMS','2024-07-24','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Circularn_24072024.pdf','Circularn_24072024.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-approval-01-2017-dust-suppression-device-approval-for-metalliferous-mines','DGMS Approval 01/2017 — Dust Suppression Device Approval for Metalliferous Mines','dgms_circular','Brings the approval of dust suppression/prevention devices fitted in drilling and boring equipment used in mines under a general approval scheme with finalized standards for their manufacture, testing and use, replacing case-by-case special orders.',null,'DGMS','2017','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Approval_Circular_SNT_01-2017636568146232411552.pdf','Approval_Circular_SNT_01-2017636568146232411552.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-compiled-2015-dgms-circulars-2015-combined','DGMS Compiled Circulars 2015 (Combined)','dgms_circular','A compilation of DGMS circulars issued during 2015, opening with the Technical (MAMID) circular on accidents and incidents due to exposure to high atmospheric temperature and heat-related disorders (heat stroke, exhaustion, cramps and syncope) among mine workers.',null,'DGMS','2015','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMS_Circulars-2015.pdf','DGMS_Circulars-2015.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-compiled-2016-dgms-circulars-2016-combined','DGMS Compiled Circulars 2016 (Combined)','dgms_circular','A compilation of DGMS circulars issued during 2016, opening with the general order permitting rescue stations and rescue rooms to maintain self-contained breathing apparatus of different types and makes under Rule 37 of the Mines Rescue Rules, 1985 subject to specified conditions.',null,'DGMS','2016','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMS_Circulars-2016.pdf','DGMS_Circulars-2016.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-exam-2018-online-examination-fee-payment-under-cmr-2017-and-mmr-1961','DGMS notice — Online payment of examination fees under CMR 2017 and MMR 1961 (2018)','dgms_circular','Administrative notice on the online payment of competency-examination fees under the Coal Mines Regulations, 2017 and Metalliferous Mines Regulations, 1961.',null,'DGMS','2018-11','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Online_Fee_Exam_Circular_Nov_2018.pdf','Online_Fee_Exam_Circular_Nov_2018.pdf',3,230,false,false),
('dgms-exam-2019-online-examination-fee-payment-under-cmr-2017-and-mmr-1961','DGMS notice — Online payment of examination fees under CMR 2017 and MMR 1961 (2019)','dgms_circular','Administrative notice on the online payment of competency-examination fees under the Coal Mines Regulations, 2017 and Metalliferous Mines Regulations, 1961.',null,'DGMS','2019','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Circular_Exam_aa2019.pdf','Circular_Exam_aa2019.pdf',3,230,false,false),
('dgms-general-01-2020-mineral-production-and-transportation-continuity','DGMS General Circular 01/2020 — Uninterrupted Mineral Production and Transportation During COVID-19 Lockdown','dgms_circular','Conveys that coal and mineral production, transportation, supply of explosives and incidental mining operations are exempted from the COVID-19 lockdown shutdown per Ministry of Home Affairs guidelines, so mining operations may continue to sustain essential production during the pandemic.',null,'DGMS','2020-03-30','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGCircularNew.pdf','DGCircularNew.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-general-2025-young-safety-innovator-recognition-program','DGMS General Circular 2025 — Young Safety Innovator Recognition Programme','dgms_circular','Invites nominations from students (under 30) and startups whose own innovations contributed to miners'' safety, to be felicitated as Young Safety Innovators of new technologies at the 125th Foundation Day of DGMS on 7 January 2026 at Dhanbad.',null,'DGMS','2025-12-03','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/cirnomition_03122025.pdf','cirnomition_03122025.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-legis-02-2017-illumination-standards-in-opencast-coal-mines','DGMS Legislative Circular 02/2017 — Standards of Illumination in Opencast Coal Mines','dgms_circular','Reproduces, for strict compliance, the standards of illumination (in lux) to be provided at different work places in opencast coal mines under Regulation 154(2) of the Coal Mines Regulations, 1957, as specified vide notification G.S.R. 617(E) dated 28.04.2017.',null,'DGMS','2017','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Cir_02_Legis_2017.pdf','Cir_02_Legis_2017.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-legis-03-2017-illumination-standards-in-opencast-metalliferous-mines','DGMS Legislative Circular 03/2017 — Standards of Illumination in Opencast Metalliferous Mines','dgms_circular','Reproduces, for strict compliance, the standards of illumination (in lux) to be provided at different work places in opencast metalliferous mines under Regulation 148(2) of the Metalliferous Mines Regulations, 1961, as specified vide notification G.S.R. 618(E) dated 28.04.2017.',null,'DGMS','2017','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Cir_03_Legis_2017.pdf','Cir_03_Legis_2017.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-legis-1-2018-emergency-escape-device-standards-in-oil-mines','DGMS Legislative Circular 1/2018 — Standard for Emergency Escape Device Used in Oil Mines','dgms_circular','Prescribes the standard for the emergency escape device, escape line and slide required on every monkey board under Regulation 38(1) of the Oil Mines Regulations, 2017, covering manufacture, materials and construction so that persons can descend safely in an emergency.',null,'DGMS','2018','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMSLegisCircular1_2018.pdf','DGMSLegisCircular1_2018.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-legis-2-2018-lifting-appliance-design-and-construction-standards-for-oil-mines','DGMS Legislative (Tech.) Circular 2/2018 — Standard for Design, Construction, Installation and Testing of Lifting Appliances in Oil Mines','dgms_circular','Prescribes the standard for the design, construction, installation and testing of lifting appliances, gear and ropes used in oil mines under Regulation 105(2)(a) of the Oil Mines Regulations, 2017, referencing BIS, ISO, OISD and API specifications for equipment and wire ropes.',null,'DGMS','2018','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMSLegisCircular2_2018.pdf','DGMSLegisCircular2_2018.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-01-2019-technical-circular-01-of-2019','DGMS (Tech) Circular 01 of 2019 — Safe conduct of operations in workover oil/gas mines','dgms_circular','Following a fatal fire at an onshore workover oil mine caused by a mobile-phone ignition of a hydrocarbon-gas cloud, this circular directs owners of oil/gas mines to provide separator vessels and flare stacks and to keep workover operations under statutory supervision, per Regulations 62(2)(c) and 129(7) of the Oil Mines Regulations, 2017.',null,'DGMS','2019','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMTechnical_2019.pdf','DGMTechnical_2019.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-01-2026-soma-related-technical-circular','DGMS (Tech)(SOMA) Circular 01 of 2026 — Preventive measures against rising mine accidents','dgms_circular','Analysing the 2022–2025 rise in fatal accidents (142/170 in coal, 144/184 in non-coal mines), this circular directs all mines to strengthen their Safety Management System against the leading causes — trackless machinery, HEMM, ground movement, explosives and falls from height.',null,'DGMS','2026-04-15','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/dgmstech26_15042026.pdf','dgmstech26_15042026.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-02-2019-technical-circular-02-of-2019','DGMS (Tech) Circular 02 of 2019 — Safety provisions for Diamond Wire Saw machines','dgms_circular','Prompted by a fatal accident in a marble mine from flying diamond beads off a snapped wire, this circular prescribes design, guarding and operating safety requirements for Diamond Wire Saw machines and ropes under Regulation 174(2) of the Metalliferous Mines Regulations, 1961.',null,'DGMS','2019','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMSCircular637127817239555988.pdf','DGMSCircular637127817239555988.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-02-2019b-technical-circular-no-2-of-2019','DGMS (Tech) Circular 02 of 2019 — Safety provisions for Diamond Wire Saw machines (Metalliferous mines & OEMs)','dgms_circular','The formally-addressed version (dated 22 November 2019) of DGMS (Tech) Circular 02 of 2019 to metalliferous-mine owners and diamond-wire-saw OEMs, setting out mandatory safety provisions for diamond wire saw machines after a fatal bead-projection accident.',null,'DGMS','2019','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Circular_No2.pdf','Circular_No2.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-02-2020-systematic-slope-monitoring-guidelines','DGMS (Tech) Circular 02 of 2020 — Guidelines for systematic monitoring of opencast slopes','dgms_circular','Issued under Regulation 106(2) of the Coal Mines Regulations, 2017, this circular standardises protocols for systematic slope-stability monitoring in opencast coal and metalliferous mines to enable timely withdrawal of men and machinery ahead of an impending slope failure.',null,'DGMS','2020-01-09','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/dgms12aa.pdf','dgms12aa.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-02-2026-soma-related-technical-circular','DGMS (Tech)(SOMA) Circular 02 of 2026 — Heat wave and high-temperature exposure precautions','dgms_circular','Consolidating earlier heat-wave advisories, this circular directs all mines to protect workers from heat stress during peak summer, prescribing recognition of heat-illness symptoms and preventive measures against high-temperature accidents.',null,'DGMS','2026-04-23','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMSTechData_23042026.pdf','DGMSTechData_23042026.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-03-2019-technical-circular-03-of-2019','DGMS (Tech) Circular 03 of 2019 — Guidelines for implementation of Safety Management Plans','dgms_circular','This circular provides guidelines for implementing (not just formulating) statutory Safety Management Plans now mandated under CMR 2017 and OMR 2017, requiring auditable documentation of controls for each identified principal hazard.',null,'DGMS','2019','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMS_Tech2019.pdf','DGMS_Tech2019.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-03-2025-heat-wave-and-high-temperature-exposure-precautions','DGMS (Tech)(OH) Circular 03 of 2025 — Heat wave and high-temperature exposure precautions','dgms_circular','Dated 28 April 2025, this circular reiterates precautions against heat-stress accidents in summer, describing the physiological effects of high atmospheric temperature (heat stroke, rash, sunburn, fatigue) and the preventive measures mines must strictly follow.',null,'DGMS','2025-04-28','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/cirsummers_28042025.pdf','cirsummers_28042025.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-04-2025-coal-metalliferous-and-oil-mine-operators-directive','DGMS (Tech)(DMRS) Circular 04 of 2025 — Emergency response and evacuation plan for mine disasters','dgms_circular','Supplementing Regulation 252 of CMR 2017, Regulation 190A of MMR 1961 and Regulation 102 of OMR 2017, this circular requires constitution of Rapid Response Teams and manned rescue stations to handle fire and disaster emergencies in coal, metalliferous and oil mines.',null,'DGMS','2025-06-19','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMS_Cirluar04_01042026.pdf','DGMS_Cirluar04_01042026.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-05-2020-safe-drilling-and-production-in-oil-and-gas-mines','DGMS (Tech) Circular 05 of 2020 — Safe conduct of drilling and production in oil and gas mines','dgms_circular','Responding to a spate of fatal hydrocarbon-gas ignition accidents at oil/gas installations, this circular frames guidelines for safe drilling and production operations, including weekly managerial supervision, defined HSE policy and controls against surcharged gas clouds.',null,'DGMS','2020-02-27','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMSTechCircular_05.pdf','DGMSTechCircular_05.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-06-2020-technical-circular-06-of-2020','DGMS (Tech) Circular 06 of 2020 — Minimum design requirements for safety features on HEMM and vehicles','dgms_circular','This circular prescribes minimum design requirements for safety features on Heavy Earth Moving Machinery and heavy/light vehicles in opencast mines, to address the rise in transport-machinery accidents under CMR 2017 and MMR 1961.',null,'DGMS','2020-02-27','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/fillll.pdf','fillll.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-07-2020-safe-conduct-of-railway-siding-operations','DGMS (Tech) Circular 07 of 2020 — Safe conduct of operations at mine railway sidings','dgms_circular','After accidents from inadvertent charging of 25kV traction lines, this circular mandates written permit-to-work and lock-out arrangements with railway authorities for loading, sampling and other work near overhead lines at mine railway sidings.',null,'DGMS','2020-03-06','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/SAFE_CONDUCT_RLY_SIDING.pdf','SAFE_CONDUCT_RLY_SIDING.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-07-2025-safety-features-in-opencast-heavy-equipment','DGMS (Tech) Circular 07 of 2025 — Safety features in HEMM and auxiliary opencast equipment','dgms_circular','Citing 2025 statistics of dumper/tipper-related fatal accidents, this circular directs opencast coal and metalliferous mines and OEMs to ensure prescribed safety features on wheeled trackless transportation machinery and auxiliary equipment.',null,'DGMS','2025-11-24','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/circular7New_24112025.pdf','circular7New_24112025.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-1-2022-high-atmospheric-temperature-exposure-incidents','DGMS (Tech)(OH) Circular 01 of 2022 — Accidents due to exposure to high atmospheric temperature','dgms_circular','This circular alerts all mines to heat-related morbidity and mortality during the 2022 heat waves and re-circulates the 2015 MAMID guidance on precautionary measures against high-atmospheric-temperature accidents.',null,'DGMS','2022-04-28','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/DGMS_TECH_CIRCULAR_OH.pdf','DGMS_TECH_CIRCULAR_OH.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-1-2023-high-temperature-exposure-accident-prevention','DGMS (Tech)(OH) Circular 01 of 2023 — Accidents due to exposure to high temperature','dgms_circular','Dated 24 April 2023, this circular requires mine managements to educate officers, supervisors and workmen on heat-related illnesses and first aid, describing the physiological effects of working in high atmospheric temperature.',null,'DGMS','2023-04-24','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Circular2023tech.pdf','Circular2023tech.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-1-2024-heat-wave-precautions-and-high-temperature-accident-prevention','DGMS (Tech)(OH) Circular 01 of 2024 — Heat wave precautions against high-temperature accidents','dgms_circular','Dated 19 April 2024, this circular sets out heat-stress symptom recognition, do''s and don''ts for treating affected miners, and administrative controls (hydration, task scheduling, protective clothing) for the summer season.',null,'DGMS','2024-04-19','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/TechCircular19042024.pdf','TechCircular19042024.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('dgms-tech-11-2020-online-annual-return-submission-via-dgms-website','DGMS (Tech) Circular 11 of 2020 — Online submission of annual returns','dgms_circular','Administrative circular notifying mines that annual returns can now be filed online through the DGMS website software module, with instructions for retrospective filing from 2015 onwards.',null,'DGMS','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/20200717205656402.pdf','20200717205656402.pdf',3,230,false,false),
