('faq-on-myths-and-realities-of-industrial-relation-ir-code-2020-dated-23-12-2025','FAQ on Myths and Realities of the Industrial Relations (IR) Code, 2020 (23 December 2025)','labour_code','This FAQ rebuts common misconceptions about the IR Code, 2020, clarifying that trade-union registration and the right to strike (with 14 days'' notice) are retained, that retrenchment protections and compensation continue, and that prior government permission for retrenchment applies to establishments with 300 or more workers.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','23-12-2025','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','FAQ on Myths and Realities of Industrial Relation (IR) Code 2020 dated 23-12-2025.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('faq-on-osh-wc-code-2020','FAQ on the Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions (OSH&WC) Code, 2020 (as on 13 March 2026)','labour_code','This FAQ clarifies the scope of the OSH&WC Code, 2020, covering applicability of central rules to dock workers at non-major ports, free pre-employment and periodic health examinations, and the division of rule-making authority between the Central and State Governments.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','FAQ on OSH&WC Code, 2020.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('faqs-code-on-wages-2019-dated-24-12-2025','FAQs on the Code on Wages, 2019 (24 December 2025)','labour_code','This FAQ explains key features of the Code on Wages, 2019, including its universal applicability across all employees, bonus eligibility for daily-wage workers, the floor-wage baseline, the revised wage definition, and the cap on total deductions at 50 percent of wages.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','24-12-2025','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','FAQs - Code on Wages, 2019 dated 24-12-2025.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('faqs-on-labour-codes-dated-30-12-2025','FAQs on the Labour Codes (30 December 2025)','labour_code','This FAQ explains transitional application of old rules, the definition of "wages" and its components, the 50 percent allowance rule, the treatment of leave encashment, and provides worked illustrations of how allowances are added back to wages under the Labour Codes.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','30-12-2025','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','FAQs on Labour Codes dated 30-12-2025.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('faqs-on-occupational-safety-health-and-working-conditions-osh-wc-code-2020-dated-19-12-202','FAQs on the Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions (OSH&WC) Code, 2020 (19 December 2025)','labour_code','This FAQ addresses concerns about the OSH&WC Code, 2020, clarifying that raising the factory and contract-labour thresholds does not remove worker protections, that 12-hour daily flexibility is subject to overtime at twice the wage, that night work for women requires consent and safeguards, and that inspector-cum-facilitators retain enforcement accountability.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','19-12-2025','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','FAQs on Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions (OSH&WC) Code, 2020 dated 19-12-2025.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('faqs-on-social-security-code-dated-09-01-2026','FAQs on the Code on Social Security, 2020 (9 January 2026)','labour_code','This FAQ clarifies the Social Security Rules, covering optional digital versus physical submission of claims, registration as an entry point to schemes, amendment of rules by notification, mandatory separate maintenance and CAG audit of Social Security Funds, and protection of maternity-benefit claims against procedural rejection.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','09-01-2026','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','FAQs on Social Security Code dated 09-01-2026.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('jharkhand-gig-worker-welfare-social-security-act-measure-2024','Jharkhand Platform Based Gig Workers (Registration and Welfare) Bill, 2024','labour_code','This Jharkhand Gazette notification (1 July 2024) publishes the draft Platform Based Gig Workers (Registration and Welfare) Bill, 2024, which proposes registration of gig workers and platforms, a Welfare Board and welfare fund, and obligations on platforms for social security, occupational safety, algorithmic transparency and dispute resolution.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2024','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Jharkhand_Gig_Worker_Social_Security_Act_2024.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('key-provisions-under-the-code-on-social-security-2020','Key Provisions under the Code on Social Security, 2020 (MoLE Circular to States/UTs, 4 January 2026)','labour_code','This Ministry of Labour and Employment communication to State and UT Labour Departments highlights the enforcement of the Code on Social Security, 2020 (from 21 November 2025) and identifies the sections under which the Central Government, State Governments and Appropriate Governments are to frame rules and schemes.',null,'Ministry of Labour & Employment','2020','in_force',null,'https://www.dgms.gov.in/','Key provisions under the Code on Social Security, 2020.pdf',3,230,true,false),
('coal-mines-regulation-1957','The Coal Mines Regulations, 1957','dgms_circular','The principal statutory regulations (S.R.O. 3419, 1957) made under the Mines Act, 1952 governing safety and operations in every coal mine in India, superseding the Indian Coal Mines Regulations, 1926.',null,'DGMS',null,'superseded','Superseded by the Coal Mines Regulations, 2017. Retained for reference.','https://www.dgms.gov.in/writereaddata/UploadFile/Coal_Mines_Regulation,_1957.pdf','Coal_Mines_Regulation,_1957.pdf',1,310,true,false),
